node.text:
We all know making mistakes in life is normal, it’s a part of living. When we make small mistakes we don’t just give up right ?

So why is it so many of us give up on our diet when we slip up? 

We transform our bodies from being consistent. Eating 1 bad meal out of 82 meals (2 weeks) of dieting isn’t going to completely ruin our progress. 

Accept the mistake and get back on your plan.

👉 WHAT’S POSSIBLE IN 8-WEEKS?
🤔 Can you really see a life changing transformation?

If you’re dedicated, like my clients above you CAN achieve big things inside 8-weeks.

But you need to be taking the RIGHT type of action.

You need:

✅ A meal plan with foods you love
✅ Workouts that suit your schedule
✅ Accountability to your goals

Can you do it on your own? Sure.

But if you want to shorten the learning curve and experience what it’s like to see results FAST… without giving up everything you enjoy in life.

👉 Click the link in my bio @ryan_spiteri and let me help you achieve your dream physique.

1️⃣ Lat Pulldown
2️⃣ Seated Cable Row
3️⃣ Barbell Row
4️⃣ Pullups

▪️ 𝗦𝗲𝘁𝘀: 4
▪️ 𝗥𝗲𝗽𝘀: 8-10
▪️ 𝗥𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗧𝗶𝗺𝗲: 90 sec

💡 Ready to become the Boss of your Body?

My new Boss Bodies Coaching Platform will be available to the public on the 24th of August.

Given the nature of this customized coaching platform, spaces upon launch will be limited, which is why I've put together a pre-launch list for you.

Click the link in my bio @ryanspitieri to join the Boss Bodies pre-launch list for free and get notified the second we go live!

node.text:
How’s your motivation to exercise?

Motivation is not just about pushing through against laziness.

It is also about dealing with the fears that you already have in your mind. Every time you are about to skip on a scheduled workout session or every time you place too much food on your plate, you should ask yourself some questions:

Why am I doing this?

What am I afraid of?

In the process of answering these questions, you will be able to reflect on your present attitude, and this will lead you to keep working on your goal.

By analyzing your thought process, you will not only help yourself prolong your motivation but also build a state of mind that allows you to control it.

Motivation is not permanent. Even if you succeeded in boosting your motivation today, you will need to do it again tomorrow. That is the nature of motivation. You have to constantly work on it.

I can help with that.

I’ve worked with thousands of people during the past five years, helping them achieve their physical goals, lose weight and pack on lean muscle mass. I’ve got room in my schedule, so why don’t we work together?

To get started, simply click the link in my bio @Ryan_Spiteri and have me as your coach.

𝗕𝗔𝗖𝗞 𝗪𝗢𝗥𝗞𝗢𝗨𝗧
📍ʙᴏᴏᴋᴍᴀʀᴋ ᴀɴᴅ sᴀᴠᴇ ↗️

1️⃣ DB Bent-Over Row Single Arm 
2️⃣ Cable Lat Pulldown
3️⃣ Machine Bent Over Row
4️⃣ Cable Close Grip Row

▪️ 𝗦𝗲𝘁𝘀: 4
▪️ 𝗥𝗲𝗽𝘀: 8-10
▪️ 𝗥𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗧𝗶𝗺𝗲: 90 sec

💡 Ready to become the Boss of your Body?

My new Boss Bodies Coaching Platform will be available to the public on the 24th of August.

Given the nature of this customized coaching platform, spaces upon launch will be limited, which is why I've put together a pre-launch list for you.

Click the link in my bio @ryanspitieri to join the Boss Bodies pre-launch list for free and get notified the second we go live!
